1Ô∏è‚É£ Provider & Resource Group
provider "azurerm" {
  features {}
}

resource "azurerm_resource_group" "rg" {
  name     = "rg-aks-demo"
  location = "East US"
}

2Ô∏è‚É£ Virtual Network & Subnet

AKS requires a subnet for cluster nodes.

resource "azurerm_virtual_network" "vnet" {
  name                = "vnet-aks"
  address_space       = ["10.1.0.0/16"]
  location            = azurerm_resource_group.rg.location
  resource_group_name = azurerm_resource_group.rg.name
}

resource "azurerm_subnet" "aks_subnet" {
  name                 = "subnet-aks"
  resource_group_name  = azurerm_resource_group.rg.name
  virtual_network_name = azurerm_virtual_network.vnet.name
  address_prefixes     = ["10.1.1.0/24"]

  delegations {
    name = "aks_delegation"
    service_delegation {
      name = "Microsoft.ContainerService/managedClusters"
      actions = ["Microsoft.Network/virtualNetworks/subnets/join/action"]
    }
  }
}


Interview points:

Subnet delegation is required for AKS

Always separate node subnets from other VNets

3Ô∏è‚É£ AKS Cluster with Managed Identity
resource "azurerm_kubernetes_cluster" "aks" {
  name                = "aks-demo"
  location            = azurerm_resource_group.rg.location
  resource_group_name = azurerm_resource_group.rg.name
  dns_prefix          = "aksdemo"

  default_node_pool {
    name       = "agentpool"
    node_count = 3
    vm_size    = "Standard_DS2_v2"
    os_disk_size_gb = 50
    type       = "VirtualMachineScaleSets"
    vnet_subnet_id = azurerm_subnet.aks_subnet.id
  }

  identity {
    type = "SystemAssigned"
  }

  network_profile {
    network_plugin    = "azure"
    load_balancer_sku = "standard"
    outbound_type     = "loadBalancer"
  }

  role_based_access_control {
    enabled = true
  }

  tags = {
    environment = "dev"
  }
}


Interview points to mention:

Managed Identity avoids service principal secrets

RBAC enabled for secure access

VM Scale Set node pool for HA & scaling

Standard Load Balancer for production

Subnet assigned for private networking

4Ô∏è‚É£ AKS Credentials Output
output "kube_config" {
  value = azurerm_kubernetes_cluster.aks.kube_config_raw
  sensitive = true
}

üîπ Optional: Private Cluster / Private Endpoint
network_profile {
  network_plugin     = "azure"
  load_balancer_sku  = "standard"
  outbound_type      = "userDefinedRouting"
  private_cluster_enabled = true
}


Makes the API server private, only accessible from the VNet

Often combined with NAT Gateway for egress
